{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1000,"text":"Let's start with day and night."},{"time":3000,"text":"Life evolved under conditions"},{"time":5000,"text":"of light and darkness,"},{"time":7000,"text":"light and then darkness."},{"time":9000,"text":"And so plants and animals"},{"time":11000,"text":"developed their own internal clocks"},{"time":13000,"text":"so that they would be ready for these changes in light."},{"time":15000,"text":"These are chemical clocks,"},{"time":17000,"text":"and they're found in every known being that has two or more cells"},{"time":20000,"text":"and in some that only have one cell."}]},{"cues":[{"time":23000,"text":"I'll give you an example --"},{"time":25000,"text":"if you take a horseshoe crab off the beach,"},{"time":27000,"text":"and you fly it all the way across the continent,"},{"time":29000,"text":"and you drop it into a sloped cage,"},{"time":32000,"text":"it will scramble up the floor of the cage"},{"time":34000,"text":"as the tide is rising"},{"time":36000,"text":"on its home shores,"},{"time":38000,"text":"and it'll skitter down again right as the water is receding"},{"time":40000,"text":"thousands of miles away."},{"time":43000,"text":"It'll do this for weeks,"},{"time":45000,"text":"until it kind of gradually loses the plot."},{"time":48000,"text":"And it's incredible to watch,"},{"time":50000,"text":"but there's nothing psychic or paranormal going on;"},{"time":52000,"text":"it's simply that these crabs have internal cycles"},{"time":55000,"text":"that correspond, usually, with what's going on around it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":60000,"text":"So, we have this ability as well."},{"time":62000,"text":"And in humans, we call it the \"body clock.\""},{"time":65000,"text":"You can see this most clearly when you take away someone's watch"},{"time":68000,"text":"and you shut them into a bunker, deep underground,"},{"time":71000,"text":"for a couple of months. (Laughter)"},{"time":73000,"text":"People actually volunteer for this,"},{"time":75000,"text":"and they usually come out"},{"time":77000,"text":"kind of raving about their productive time in the hole."},{"time":79000,"text":"So, no matter how atypical these subjects would have to be,"},{"time":82000,"text":"they all show the same thing."},{"time":84000,"text":"They get up just a little bit later every day -- say 15 minutes or so --"},{"time":87000,"text":"and they kind of drift all the way around the clock like this"},{"time":90000,"text":"over the course of the weeks."},{"time":92000,"text":"And so, in this way we know that they are working on their own internal clocks,"},{"time":95000,"text":"rather than somehow sensing the day outside."}]},{"cues":[{"time":99000,"text":"So fine, we have a body clock,"},{"time":101000,"text":"and it turns out that it's incredibly important in our lives."},{"time":104000,"text":"It's a huge driver for culture"},{"time":106000,"text":"and I think that it's the most underrated force on our behavior."},{"time":112000,"text":"We evolved as a species near the equator,"},{"time":114000,"text":"and so we're very well-equipped"},{"time":116000,"text":"to deal with 12 hours of daylight"},{"time":118000,"text":"and 12 hours of darkness."},{"time":120000,"text":"But of course, we've spread to every corner of the globe"},{"time":122000,"text":"and in Arctic Canada, where I live,"},{"time":124000,"text":"we have perpetual daylight in summer"},{"time":126000,"text":"and 24 hours of darkness in winter."},{"time":129000,"text":"So the culture, the northern aboriginal culture,"},{"time":132000,"text":"traditionally has been highly seasonal."},{"time":134000,"text":"In winter, there's a lot of sleeping going on;"},{"time":137000,"text":"you enjoy your family life inside."},{"time":139000,"text":"And in summer, it's almost manic hunting"},{"time":142000,"text":"and working activity very long hours,"},{"time":144000,"text":"very active."}]},{"cues":[{"time":147000,"text":"So, what would our natural rhythm look like?"},{"time":149000,"text":"What would our sleeping patterns be"},{"time":152000,"text":"in the sort of ideal sense?"},{"time":155000,"text":"Well, it turns out"},{"time":157000,"text":"that when people are living"},{"time":159000,"text":"without any sort of artificial light at all,"},{"time":161000,"text":"they sleep twice every night."},{"time":163000,"text":"They go to bed around 8:00 p.m."},{"time":165000,"text":"until midnight"},{"time":167000,"text":"and then again, they sleep"},{"time":169000,"text":"from about 2:00 a.m. until sunrise."},{"time":172000,"text":"And in-between, they have a couple of hours"},{"time":174000,"text":"of sort of meditative quiet in bed."},{"time":177000,"text":"And during this time,"},{"time":179000,"text":"there's a surge of prolactin,"},{"time":181000,"text":"the likes of which a modern day never sees."},{"time":184000,"text":"The people in these studies"},{"time":186000,"text":"report feeling so awake during the daytime,"},{"time":188000,"text":"that they realize"},{"time":190000,"text":"they're experiencing true wakefulness"},{"time":192000,"text":"for the first time in their lives."}]},{"cues":[{"time":194000,"text":"So, cut to the modern day."},{"time":196000,"text":"We're living in a culture of jet lag,"},{"time":198000,"text":"global travel,"},{"time":200000,"text":"24-hour business,"},{"time":203000,"text":"shift work."},{"time":206000,"text":"And you know, our modern ways"},{"time":208000,"text":"of doing things"},{"time":210000,"text":"have their advantages,"},{"time":212000,"text":"but I believe we should understand the costs."}]},{"cues":[{"time":215000,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":217000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}